CI/CD Pipeline Flow

This project uses a multi-stage Azure DevOps YAML pipeline to build and deploy an application.

Continuous Integration (CI)

The pipeline is triggered when code is pushed or a pull request is created for the main branch

It installs Node.js and runs basic build steps using a template

Test results are published (if available)

A pipeline artifact named drop is created and stored

The build output is packaged and published to the Azure Artifacts feed (lab08-feed)

Continuous Deployment (CD)
Deploy to Dev

Runs automatically after the CI stage

Downloads the artifact created in the CI stage

Simulates deployment to the lab08-dev environment

Deploy to UAT

Runs after the Dev stage

Requires manual approval before execution

Deploys the same artifact to the lab08-uat environment

Key Points

Single build is reused across environments

Artifacts ensure consistency between deployments

Approval is required before UAT deployment

Secrets are managed using a variable group

Flow Summary
Code Push / PR → CI (Build + Test + Artifact + Package)
                     ↓
               Deploy Dev
                     ↓
             Deploy UAT (Manual Approval)
